<p>I have timestamp stored in MySQL in following format:</p>  <pre><code>$if_modified_since = date('Y-m-d H:i:s'); </code></pre>  <p>The timestamp is saved using server's default timezone which in my case is <code>EST</code>. I need to send a <code>CURL</code> request with <code>if-modified-since</code> header.</p>  <pre><code>curl_setopt($ch, CURLOPT_HTTPHEADER, array("If-Modified-Since: ".gmdate('D, d M Y H:i:s \G\M\T',$if_modified_since))); </code></pre>  <p>What will be the most optimal way for me to convert time in <code>EST</code> to <code>GMT</code>? Also is there a way to make it totally generic by checking the server timezone (instead of just hard-coding in <code>EST</code>)?</p>